 This is a single center prospective randomized double blinded placebo controlled study.

 The primary aim of the study is to optimize the intraoperative treatment protocol for head and neck cancer patients to reduce the incidence of delirium and associated postoperative cognitive dysfunction.

 Secondary aims are to determine the dose response relationship for intraoperative ketamine and delirium reduction, determine if a single dose of ketamine will reduce post-operative pain and opioid requirements, determine if raw electroencephalogram (EEG) data can predict postoperative delirium during general anesthesia, and to evaluate length of intensive care unit (ICU) and length of hospital stay.

